0% increase in biofilms in vacuum\nspace compared to porous materials, and 128% more biofilms in the target growth\nregion for PM-induced biofilm growth compared with the vacuum space growth. Our\nwork provides deeper insights into bio-porous materials design, optimization\nprocess characterizations, and extracting new mechanisms from the\noptimizations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 15 May 2023 12:01:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-16"}
